{"parse":{"title":"Rodrigo de Jerez","pageid":5192102,"revid":812027455,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rodrigo_de_Jerez.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/38/Rodrigo_de_Jerez.jpg/220px-Rodrigo_de_Jerez.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"187\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/38/Rodrigo_de_Jerez.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"243\" data-file-height=\"207\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Rodrigo_de_Jerez.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Rodrigo de Jerez</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Rodrigo de Jerez</b> was one of the <a href=\"/wiki/Spain\" title=\"Spain\">Spanish</a> crewmen who sailed to the <a href=\"/wiki/Americas\" title=\"Americas\">Americas</a> on the <a href=\"/wiki/Santa_Mar%C3%ADa_(ship)\" title=\"Santa Mar\u00eda (ship)\">Santa Maria</a> as part of <a href=\"/wiki/Christopher_Columbus\" title=\"Christopher Columbus\">Christopher Columbus</a>'s first voyage across the <a href=\"/wiki/Atlantic_Ocean\" title=\"Atlantic Ocean\">Atlantic Ocean</a> in 1492. He is credited with being the first European <a href=\"/wiki/Tobacco_smoking\" title=\"Tobacco smoking\">smoker</a>. \n</p><p>On 12 October 1492, the crew first encountered tobacco at <a href=\"/wiki/San_Salvador_Island\" title=\"San Salvador Island\">San Salvador</a> island in the <a href=\"/wiki/Bahamas\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bahamas\">Bahamas</a>, known to the natives as <a href=\"/wiki/Guanahani\" title=\"Guanahani\">Guanahani</a>. The natives presented them with apparently valuable \"dry leaves that spread a peculiar fragrance\". The crew later discarded the leaves.\n</p><p>In November 1492, Jerez and <a href=\"/wiki/Luis_de_Torres\" title=\"Luis de Torres\">Luis de Torres</a> first observed natives smoking.  They were searching for the <a href=\"/wiki/Emperor_of_China\" title=\"Emperor of China\">Emperor of China</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hongzhi_Emperor\" title=\"Hongzhi Emperor\">Hongzhi Emperor</a>, in <a href=\"/wiki/Cuba\" title=\"Cuba\">Cuba</a>. Apparently, the natives made rolls of palm and mais leaves \"in the manner of a musket formed of paper\" with tobacco on the inside. One would light one side and \"drink\" the smoke out of the other.\n</p><p>Jerez picked up the tobacco smoking habit. When he returned to Europe in the <a href=\"/wiki/Ni%C3%B1a\" title=\"Ni\u00f1a\">Ni\u00f1a</a>, he introduced the habit to his home town, <a href=\"/wiki/Ayamonte\" title=\"Ayamonte\">Ayamonte</a>. The smoke surrounding him frightened his neighbours: the <a href=\"/wiki/Spanish_Inquisition\" title=\"Spanish Inquisition\">Spanish Inquisition</a> imprisoned him for his \"<a href=\"/wiki/Sinful\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sinful\">sinful</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Hell\" title=\"Hell\">infernal</a>\" habits<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>, because \"only <a href=\"/wiki/Devil\" title=\"Devil\">Devil</a> could give a man the power to exhale smoke from his mouth\"<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (June 2016)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>. When he was released seven years later, smoking tobacco had caught on.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rodrigo_de_Jerez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://historiek.net/rodrigo-de-jerez-de-eerste-roker-van-europa/42350/\">\"Rodrigo de Jerez, de eerste roker van Europa\"</a>. Historiek<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">25 November</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Rodrigo+de+Jerez%2C+de+eerste+roker+van+Europa&amp;rft.pub=Historiek&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fhistoriek.net%2Frodrigo-de-jerez-de-eerste-roker-van-europa%2F42350%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARodrigo+de+Jerez\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Rodrigo_de_Jerez&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://history-world.org/Columbus,%20List%20of%20Sailors.htm\">List of Officers and Sailors in the First Voyage of Columbus</a> at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://history-world.org\">history-world.org</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1242\nCached time: 20180910042043\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.096 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.147 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 264/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 3464/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 542/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 11/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursi